This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with wireless power transfer in wireless networks. Additionally, the paper involves the study of distributed charging control, which is a key aspect of network architecture and design. 

The paper may also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the study of channel estimation and power allocation in a broadband wireless power transfer network. 

Furthermore, the paper may belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves the design of a distributed charging control protocol for maximizing network lifetime. 

The paper may also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia) as it deals with the charging of wireless devices, which are often used for multimedia applications. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.PE (Performance) as it involves the study of network lifetime and the design of a protocol to maximize it.
